article.headline: Morehead St. 77, ETSU 56
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. (AP) -- Quentin Pryor scored a career high 24 points as Morehead State beat East Tennessee State 77-56 Tuesday night at Johnson Arena. Pryor also grabbed eight rebounds, three assists, three blocks and five 3-pointers for Morehead State, which improved to 2-2. The Eagles led 39-29 at the half and extended their lead to 66-48 with 4:47 left on free throws by Pryor. Shaun Williams and Cody Ballard also finished with double-figures with 16 and 10 points, respectively. Williams added 10 rebounds, four assists, three blocks and three steals. For ETSU (2-3), Brad Knuckles earned 14 points. Dequan Twilley, the Bucs starting guard, did not play in Tuesdays game. The university said Twilley was attending to family matters.
